sec.p:
            Here, we develop the proof-of-concept of an autonomous material with properties that are temporally programmed by biological signaling molecules using protein components derived from the cyanobacterial circadian clock (Fig. 
            1
            ). In their natural context, KaiA, KaiB, and KaiC proteins generate a self-sustaining ~24-h rhythm that is used to synchronize physiology with the external light-dark cycle. Moreover, these proteins can be removed from their cellular context and can generate stable oscillations in a reconstituted in vitro system

              14
              ,
              27
              , 
              28
              –
              29

            .

