                1051 pixels

                  57

                , such that all pixel values were converted to 1 or 0. To measure cluster sizes, we identified each connected set of pixels above threshold as a cluster and count the number of pixels in each such region. By dividing the number of pixels within each 2D area by the maximum cross-sectional area of a colloid, we estimated the size of each cluster in terms of the minimum number of colloids it comprises. To quantify the distribution of cluster sizes we evaluated the cumulative distribution function of cluster sizes across all images for a given time point and condition (Fig. 
                S7F
                 and 
                S8
                ).

